	id="Sub_DistanceR">
	<title>Distance between Numbers: Illustration</title>
	<sub.page.body>
		<block>
			<para>If we know that <latex>s\leq t</latex> are numbers in <latex>\RNr</latex>, it makes sense to define the distance from <latex>s</latex> to <latex>t</latex> to be <latex>\Dstnc{s}{t}:=t-s</latex>. If, however, <latex>s,t\in \RNr</latex> are arbitrary and we don't know which of the two is bigger, we can use the identity of absolute values</para>
			<computation>
				<left>\Abs{ t-s }</left>
				<center>=</center>
				<right>\Abs{ s-t }</right>
			</computation>
			<para>to make a definition of distance between the two numbers</para>
			<figure>
				<img src="ims/DistanceNumbers.png"></img>
			</figure>
		</block>
	</sub.page.body>
</sub.page>